1 4. The mineral developer shall reimburse the reasonable actual costs of the required
2 appraisal incurred by the surface owner for obtaining a required appraisal under this
3 section or, at the election of the surface owner, the mineral developer shall pay the
4 reasonable actual costs directly to the appraiser.
5 5. The required appraisal or opinion of value expressed in the required appraisal is
6 inadmissible at a proceeding commenced under this chapter, unless the information is
7 offered by the surface owner. Whether an appraisal is issued under this section does
8 not require or prohibit the introduction of specific evidence offered at a proceeding
9 commenced under this chapter.
10 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 38-11.1-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is
11 amended and reenacted as follows:
12 38-11.1-09. Rejection - Legal action - Fees and costs.
13 If the person seeking compensation rejects the offer of the mineral developer, that person
14 may bring an action for compensation in the court of proper jurisdiction. If the amount of
15 compensation awarded by the court is greater than that which had beenthe amount offered by
16 the mineral developer, the court shall award the person seeking compensation reasonable
17 attorney's fees, any costs assessed by the court and disbursements under chapter 28 - 26 , and
18 interest on the amount of the final compensation awarded by the court from the day drilling is
19 commenced. The rate of interest awarded must be the prime rate charged by the Bank of North
20 Dakota on the date of the judgment.
